review_blob: Tastes a little like liquid bread.  I know Im gonna get flamed for this,  but I actually prefer Corona.  Not a bad beer though.  Im drinking one right now...

For some reason in my younger beer-drinking days I used to love this beer.  It was my favorite.  Now either Ive changed or the beer has changed (it could be actually that the beer has changed),  but it is now just so-so.  Not too bad though,  I still drink it.  It seems as if after I started appreciating it so much that it started catching on in a big way here in the U.S.  I wouldnt be surprised if the company took advantage of its new-found volume and decided to cut costs and produce a lesser beer.

This beer used to be the best Mexican beer ever.  But now they changed something.  The new batches are merely "pretty damn good".  The old Bohemia used to have thicker gold foil around the cap,  that wasnt glued on.  I guess theyre cutting costs and producing a beer that isnt quite as good as the old one.  Still pretty damn good though.
This beer is one of the best Mexican beers.  I am not generally a fan of dark beers like this,  but for this Ill make an exception.
